fields.Title: WHIRLING / DREAM1
fields.Description: Adrift in an alcohol induced oblivion, the faculties of your mind speak to you.

fields.Title: START
input
You: "Look, there's *I Am Tired of Being..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look, there's *I Am Tired of Being This Type of Animal* and Who-Gives-a-Shit!

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "An inordinate amount of time passes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An inordinate amount of time passes.  It is utterly void of struggle. No ex-wives are contained within it.

fields.Title: You: "I like nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: I like nothing.

fields.Title: You: "That sounds like something I would..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That sounds like something I would like to do -- let's go!

fields.Title: Limbic System: "You lost."
fields.Dialogue Text: You lost.

fields.Title: You: "I want to get off now, I like pain..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I want to get off now, I like pain and burning light and wanting things from people who don't want to give them to me.

fields.Title: You: "How big is the ball?"
fields.Dialogue Text: How big is the ball?

fields.Title: You: "And this *dukin' it out* I keep hea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And this *dukin' it out* I keep hearing about - what's that?

fields.Title: Limbic System: "Yes, you're one disco mother."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, you're one disco mother.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Fear and apprehension... You should..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Fear and apprehension... You should ask what's out there first.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "You got it, sweet brother! Nothing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You got it, sweet brother! Nothing upon nothing, upon nothing!

fields.Title: Limbic System: "There's this giant ball there. And..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's this giant ball there. And evil apes. And the evil apes are dukin' it out on the ball. You're one of them. It's basically all just evil apes dukin' it out on a giant ball.

fields.Title: You: "Who *am* I? What sort of creature d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Who *am* I? What sort of creature does this to their own mouth?!

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Like a fly to the ointment, your co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Like a fly to the ointment, your conscience sticks to it. The limbed and headed machine of pain and undignified suffering is firing up again. It wants to walk the desert. Hurting. Longing. Dancing to disco music.

fields.Title: You: "Don't be naive, of course not. I wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't be naive, of course not. I want to sail the inky blackness until forever ends!

fields.Title: Limbic System: "Infinitesimally small."
fields.Dialogue Text: Infinitesimally small.

fields.Title: Getting off point
Jump to: [Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Somewhere in the sore, bloated man-..."]
You: "Allons-y! Never let me go!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Allons-y! Never let me go!

fields.Title: Untitled hub
Jump to: [Untitled hub (03)]
You: "How about you cough up some more of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: How about you cough up some more of that sweet oblivion?

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Coming right up, sir. Smooth passag..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Coming right up, sir. Smooth passage...

fields.Title: Limbic System: "An awareness creeps up on you. A ma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An awareness creeps up on you. A mass lies hidden in your dead angle, soaking in some lurid, acidic sauce. It's bloated and shameful, a ball of meat surrounding you... This is a terrible line of questioning, and it will only lead to more awareness of the meat-thing.

fields.Title: You: "Stop! I don't want to hear anything..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stop! I don't want to hear anything more about this *sensation*. Take me back to the formless, disembodied nothing!
fields.Alternate1: Please, no! I changed my mind! Take me back to the formless, disembodied nothing!

fields.Title: You: "No, I want to get off now. I like p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, I want to get off now. I like pain and burning light and wanting things from people who don't want to give them to me.

fields.Title: You: "I do. Let me off."
fields.Dialogue Text: I do. Let me off.

fields.Title: You: "Help! Someone! Cut my head off, it'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Help! Someone! Cut my head off, it's trying to murder the rest of me!

fields.Title: Untitled hub
You: "(Simply keep on non-existing.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: (Simply keep on non-existing.)

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "I know you do, baby... I know..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I know you do, baby... I know...

fields.Title: Limbic System: "Yes, it is. And you drowned in that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes, it is. And you drowned in that sadness a long time ago.

fields.Title: Volition: "You can take it, you're a Champion!"
fields.Dialogue Text: You can take it, you're a Champion!

fields.Title: Untitled hub (02)
You: "This is great!"
fields.Dialogue Text: This is great!

fields.Title: Limbic System: "You wouldn't like it if I told you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You wouldn't like it if I told you what's back there. Why do you think you had to bludgeon yourself into oblivion? Or did you not sense yourself -- marinating? Poured so much over yourself... Got a bit *carried away* did we, chef?

fields.Title: You: "No, I wanted to know about the ex-s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, I wanted to know about the ex-something.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Ever."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ever.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "All right. Nothingtown to Fuck-All-..."
fields.Dialogue Text: All right. Nothingtown to Fuck-All-Borough!

fields.Title: You: "No, I am not scared, I am a Champio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, I am not scared, I am a Champion!

fields.Title: Variable["whirling.dreamone_longroute"]
Variable["whirling.dreamone_longroute"]
!(Variable["whirling.dreamone_longroute"])
Ancient Reptilian Brain: "There is nothing. Only warm, primor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is nothing. Only warm, primordial blackness. Your conscience ferments in it -- no larger than a single grain of malt. You don't have to do anything anymore.

fields.Title: You: "A return trip to The Silence please..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A return trip to The Silence please!

fields.Title: You: "Tell me, what's waiting for me?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Tell me, what's waiting for me?

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "The song of death is sweet and endl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The song of death is sweet and endless... But what is this? Somewhere in the sore, bloated *man-meat* around you -- a sensation!

fields.Title: You: "(Plunge back into the fathomless de..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Plunge back into the fathomless deep.)

fields.Title: You: "Let's visit the ancient Zero-Holm!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Let's visit the ancient Zero-Holm!

fields.Title: You: "I don't care, I'm an idiot. A brave..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I don't care, I'm an idiot. A brave idiot.

fields.Title: Limbic System: "Vying for resources? It's just a st..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Vying for resources? It's just a stupid expression you picked up somewhere. The part of the presentation you want to take home with you is this: you have to beat the other evil apes in the face or you lose.

fields.Title: You: "Never ever ever?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Never ever ever?

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Do you really?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Do you really?

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Not you! Your days of giving a shit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not you! Your days of giving a shit and being that type of animal are over.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "There. No ball of meat, no light in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There. No ball of meat, no light in the formless nothing. Just nightswimming!

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Somehow you know what it is -- a Co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Somehow you know what it is -- a Coupris Kineema motor carriage.

fields.Title: Limbic System: "You can't even make out it's a ball..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can't even make out it's a ball, when you're dukin' it out. It's that large.

fields.Title: You: "Allons-y, let's go!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Allons-y, let's go!

fields.Title: You: "How small are the apes?"
fields.Dialogue Text: How small are the apes?

fields.Title: You: "That's sad."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's sad.

fields.Title: You: "What was that about the *ex-* somet..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What was that about the *ex-* something?

fields.Title: You: "Wait, I did this to myself?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, I did this to myself?

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Ex-love, ex-tenderness. It is fooli..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ex-love, ex-tenderness. It is foolish of you to resurface to the loss. Not after all the damage you suffered to get here, some of it irreversible... Stay, sail with me through the Abyssopelagic Zone!

fields.Title: You: "Okay, I'm a bit scared now. Let's g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Okay, I'm a bit scared now. Let's go back to the dark.

fields.Title: You: "Mother, help me, there's a head att..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Mother, help me, there's a head attached to my neck and I'm *in* it.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "The sound outside -- you recognize..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sound outside -- you recognize it. It's a Coupris Kineema motor carriage.

fields.Title: You: "Wait, no! I need to belittle myself..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, no! I need to belittle myself instead.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Never ever."
fields.Dialogue Text: Never ever.

fields.Title: You: "What do you mean *drowned*?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What do you mean *drowned*?

fields.Title: Limbic System: "A fiery streak penetrates your skul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A fiery streak penetrates your skull, trying to force your eyes open. It's a sound. A clarion call from hell.

fields.Title: You: "Gimme some more."
fields.Dialogue Text: Gimme some more.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Somewhere in the sore, bloated man-..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Somewhere in the sore, bloated man-meat around you -- *a sensation*!

fields.Title: You: "[Open your eyes.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Open your eyes.]

fields.Title: Untitled hub (03)
Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Do you want me to upgrade that into..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Do you want me to upgrade that into a *one way trip*, sir?

fields.Title: You: "Don't stop, keep singing. Sing me t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't stop, keep singing. Sing me the song of death.

fields.Title: Limbic System: "The stench of liquor rises from you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The stench of liquor rises from your mouth. And with it -- an *un-godly* headache.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Never ever ever ever, baby!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Never ever ever ever, baby!

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Yes. It. Is."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. It. Is.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "Great choice, elder one. It has alw..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Great choice, elder one. It has always been like this -- and it always will.
